    {
      "id": "34d543366d086af39365363f041910609820e8a6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 284,
        "name": "Emoly Liu",
        "email": "emoly@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "liuying_emoly"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-04 06:22:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nThe patch caused sanity.sh test_154d regression. Please modify the related  test script as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8b160b1786141e2ca9755570030afb0cfdbeaaef",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-07 15:55:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, It is. Can we use one nid_stat for multi-client with same nid?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b243f0fc39fb814d944bb48d5b5c6442ea6e616b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-07 20:09:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIf I understand this correctly, it will break all tools that are using the per-NID statistics. Also, the only time there are multiple mounts on the same NID will be during testing. \n\nThere isn't enough explanation in the patch or the bug to say why this is really needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c122c8368d9faff54dae3f10d174f4e1dabaa519",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-11 17:41:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, It really broken scripts what using nid to get data. What i encountered issue is that lwp device and ofd device also create nid_stats under exports entry. So we are not only face issue when multi-client connect with same nid, but also client work with mdt or ost on same node. Of course,  This case also rarely presents often. I just found sanity-133e failed when testing on local box(This means client, mdt&ost using same node).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c74844964dcf73d14b688a9786392430249fe04b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-18 03:57:25.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
